WEBVTT

1.1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.022
Trust is won in the first two minutes.

1.2
00:00:04.022 --> 00:00:08.044
Here's the proof you carry into every conversation.

2.1
00:00:08.044 --> 00:00:16.650
Magppie was honoured at KBIS twenty-twenty-six in Orlando — the world's largest Kitchen and Bath Industry Show.

2.2
00:00:16.650 --> 00:00:25.256
We won the Most Unexpected Innovation award, placing alongside global leaders like Caesarstone and LG.

3.1
00:00:25.256 --> 00:00:31.294
One correction worth remembering: the award is Most Unexpected Innovation — not 'Most Innovative Kitchen Brand'.

3.2
00:00:31.294 --> 00:00:37.332
Precision builds credibility.

4.1
00:00:37.332 --> 00:00:41.365
Our kitchens are trusted by the Ambanis, M.

4.2
00:00:41.365 --> 00:00:45.398
S.

4.3
00:00:45.398 --> 00:00:49.430
Dhoni, Ranbir Kapoor, Shilpa Shetty, and business leaders like Peyush Bansal of Lenskart.

4.4
00:00:49.430 --> 00:00:53.463
But here's the rule: use two or three names, maximum.

4.5
00:00:53.463 --> 00:00:57.496
Never read the whole list — it sounds like a script.

5.1
00:00:57.496 --> 00:01:09.066
When there is no showroom nearby, trust comes from systems: central manufacturing with uniform standards, in-house installation teams, written commitments, and pan-India guarantees.

5.2
00:01:09.066 --> 00:01:20.636
Then always offer one of three things — a sample to their home, a video call with an expert, or a visit to a customer installation near them.

6.1
00:01:20.636 --> 00:01:25.653
Note these three things.

6.2
00:01:25.653 --> 00:01:30.670
One — the award is Most Unexpected Innovation, KBIS twenty-twenty-six, Orlando.

6.3
00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:35.686
Two — celebrity names: two or three per conversation, never the whole list.

6.4
00:01:35.686 --> 00:01:40.703
Three — no showroom nearby?

6.5
00:01:40.703 --> 00:01:45.720
Offer a sample delivery, an expert video call, or a customer site visit.

7.1
00:01:45.720 --> 00:01:48.974
Proof, precision, and three concrete offers.

7.2
00:01:48.974 --> 00:01:52.228
Quiz time.

